Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: FlowMingle is a new take on online dating that is inherently social and group oriented. FlowMingle abandons the notion of a 'profile' and the over-promising of personality tests, and instead relies on daily group interaction to create an inherently social and engaging experience.  FlowMingle intelligently places people in small local groups that interact with each other during a five day guided introduction process. Each day the group is presented an ice-breaker question that is designed to encourage interpersonal communication, spark interest, and help people get to know each other in a meaningful way.  Group members can also send personal messages that may be received on a mobile phone. At the end of the introduction process, group members decide who they would like to communicate one-on-one with.  FlowMingle helps members initiate communication, plan a meeting, and stay in contact.

Description: SMASH is a free of cost, STEM-intensive college preparatory program for underrepresented high school students of color.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: SMASH is the flagship project of the Level Playing Field Institute (LPFI).The Summer Math and Science Honors Academy (SMASH) is a free of cost, STEM-intensive college preparatory program for underrepresented high school students of color. SMASH boasts a rigorous 5-week, 3-year summer, fully residential STEM enrichment program which provides access to STEM coursework and access to mentors, role models, and support networks of students of color. Each summer, SMASH scholars spend five weeks on a college campus immersed in STEM and live among other high-potential, underrepresented (African American, Latino/a, Native American, Southeast Asian or Pacific Islander, low-income, first-in-family to attend college) high school students. In addition to their summer courses, SMASH scholars remain engaged during the school year through monthly STEM workshops and academic programming. This includes SAT prep, college counseling, financial aid workshops, and other activities to ensure continued academic success.
Industry Groups: Education, Information Technology, Other, Social Impact, Software
